      <memberdef kind="function" id="classspibus_1a02fd73d861ef2e4aabb38c0c9ff82947" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>void</type>
        <definition>void init</definition>
        <argsstring>()</argsstring>
        <name>init</name>
        <briefdescription>
<para>The init function. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<para>In case initialization still has been performed, indicated by flag init_done the function returns immediately, otherwise chip select gpios will be assigned by call of macro GPIO_DT_SPEC_GET and delay set to 0. The SPI controller device structure will be retrieved by calling macro DEVICE_DT_GET and function checks if the device is ready for usage with call of function device_is_ready. The return value of this function will be assigned to flag device_good. In case of an error a debug message at error level will be printed. Finally operation mode is set to loop mode, clock frequency is set to 8 MHz and chip select configuration is assigned before init_done flag is set to true. <simplesect kind="note"><para>Adjustment of clock frequency for FRAM SPI is done here with line spi_cfg.frequency = 8000000U; The value must be unsigned integer in Hz. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
