    <briefdescription>
<para>SPI bus driver class implemented according to C++ singleton design pattern. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<para><simplesect kind="par"><title>Detailed Description </title><para>The SPI bus class handles the initialization of the attached SPI slave and the communication over the SPI bus. Major part of configuration and initialization is located in the device tree, other parts are located in the init function of this class. storage of the acceleration raw See details in <ulink url="https://docs.zephyrproject.org/latest/kernel/drivers/index.html">Device Driver Model documentation</ulink> and in <ulink url="https://docs.zephyrproject.org/apidoc/latest/group__spi__interface.html">API documentation</ulink> <linebreak/>
 The spibus class provides the init method. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
